{"word":"G1971 - ἐπιποθέω - epipothéō - ep-ee-poth-eh'-o - Desire","slug":"G1971","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἐπιποθέω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>epipothéō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ep-ee-poth-eh'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Desire"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B5;&#x0313;&#x03C0;&#x03B9;&#x03C0;&#x03BF;&#x03B8;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03C9; - epipotheo&#x0304;</b> - <i>ep-ee-poth-eh'-o</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G1909\">G1909</a> and <b>&#x03C0;&#x03BF;&#x03B8;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03C9;</b> <b>potheo&#x0304;</b> (to <i>yearn</i>); to <i>dote upon</i>, that is, <i>intensely crave</i> possession (lawfully or wrongfully): - (earnestly) desire (greatly), (greatly) long (after), lust."}]}